1. 3.Comparable Book

Expand Book by implementing **Comparable\&lt;Book\&gt;**

Book have to be **compared by name**. When name is equal, **compare** them by **year.**

Expand **Book** from **UML diagram** below:

| **\&lt;\&lt;Comparable\&lt;Book\&gt;\&gt;\&gt;**** Book** |
| --- |
| - | title: String |
| - | year: int |
| - | authors: List\&lt;String\&gt; |
| - | setTitle(String) |
| - | setYear(String) |
| - | setAuthors(String…) |
| + | getTitle(): String |
| + | getYear(): int |
| + | getAuthors(): List\&lt;String\&gt; |
| + | **compareTo(Book): int** |

You can use only **one constructor**. Authors can be **anonymous, one or many**.

### Examples

| Main.java |
| --- |
| **public static void** main(String[] args) {
    Book bookOne = **new** Book( **&quot;Animal Farm&quot;** , 2003, **&quot;George Orwell&quot;** );
    Book bookThree = **new** Book( **&quot;The Documents in the Case&quot;** , 2002);
    Book bookTwo = **new** Book( **&quot;The Documents in the Case&quot;** , 1930, **&quot;Dorothy Sayers&quot;** , **&quot;Robert Eustace&quot;** );

     **if** (bookOne.compareTo(bookTwo) \&gt; 0) {
        System. **out**.println(String._format_( **&quot;%s is before %s&quot;** , bookOne, bookTwo));
    } **else if** (bookOne.compareTo(bookTwo) \&lt; 0) {
        System. **out**.println(String._format_( **&quot;%s is before %s&quot;** , bookTwo, bookOne));
    } **else** {
        System. **out**.println( **&quot;Book are equal&quot;** );
    }
} |

1. 4.Book Comparator

Create a class **BookComparator** from **UML diagram** below:

| **\&lt;\&lt;Comparator\&lt;Book\&gt;\&gt;\&gt;**** BookComparator** |
| --- |
| + | **compare(Book, Book): int** |

**BookComparator** have to **compare** two books by:

1. Book title
2. Year of publishing a book



### Examples

| Main.java |
| --- |
| **public static void** main(String[] args) {
    Book bookOne = **new** Book( **&quot;Animal Farm&quot;** , 2003, **&quot;George Orwell&quot;** );
    Book bookThree = **new** Book( **&quot;The Documents in the Case&quot;** , 2002);
    Book bookTwo = **new** Book( **&quot;The Documents in the Case&quot;** , 1930, **&quot;Dorothy Sayers&quot;** , **&quot;Robert Eustace&quot;** );

    List\&lt;Book\&gt; books = **new** ArrayList\&lt;\&gt;();
    books.add(bookOne);
    books.add(bookTwo);
    books.add(bookThree);

    books.sort( **new** BookComparator());

 **   for** (Book book : books) {
        System. **out**.println(book.getTitle() + book.getYear());
    }
} |
